tip.text: Alamack fish burger was of gd size and palatable too with right crispness and tender and the mayonnaise just go well. Except a little exp for $12 a burger and have to top $5 for chips and drink .

Portobello w soft charcoal bun n fries.rm was juicy with huge portion of spinach leaves and puree. Well blended . Avocado cheesecake w light hint of avocado and cheese is dense and creamy. Bk for more
Vegetarian cuisine . Pumpkin soup/ star pizza with chessy crust/ porchinic pasta well olive , macaroni alfredo casserole .deserts not their Forte . Main dishes okay .
Kaizen pizza with silver fish / seafood and the flavoring and crust was just to perfection and their recommended as well !squid spaghetti with cod roe on the other hand was a bit dry .
Iced walnut brownie latte and earl grey passion mojito with pcs of ny cheesecake 2 spend wkend. Always packed ! Cute 3D latte art !!
Concentrated Forest rm soup served in toasted bread bowl was nice with generous slices of rms...nonya otah bread fared badly with miserable bits of otah.
Cajun spiced chicken burger patty slightly  burnt.fish and chip nicely cooked. Beef burger was of decent portion.fries served was generous . Bushrusmint is recommended  but I much preferred coffee.
Free test tube fruit juice. Veg spag was appetizing wit pepper/bringal/rm. .truffle fries wif mayo dip was gd.Masago caviar pasta wit scallops n broken quail egg. A tad pricey, but high recommended!
Frozen grapefruit kreme beer is damn silky and smooth ..along with sides ..normal sweet potato / spicy pollock is chewy and goes well with beer ..chicken wings with thick sweet Korean sauce
French Toast with caramelized nuts.texture is soft custard-like in Centre with sliced bananas and cream.Not fantastic as raved abt.hoshino coffee is arabica roasted hand drip- taste strong and clean
Latte was damn small cup for that price charged ..Sicilian cake was damm nice with layers of well filled chocloate / hazelnut mousse and hazelnut base . Not too sweet for sugar intolerance fellas
herbal soup base with tau pok, vegetarian meat ,fish ball  fresh veggies.  Herbal soup was not bitter and..Taiwan bean paste noodle was mediocre ..lose out to Korean bean paste noodle as felt.

formattedAddress: Paya Lebar Square (60 Paya Lebar Road)

tip.text: Had cold brewed coffee .hot coffee will had release the aroma I tik.  Took the peach turnover. ..kinda hard ... will be better if much more moist texture . Wil be back for the main n hot beverage !

venue.name: Chye Seng Huat Hardware Coffee Bar

tip.text: Vegetarian lasange is over filled with delicious veggies wif layer of pasta .well baked with cheese. Sticky date pudding with toffee is another recommended .. bits of date would be savored in mouth.

Catfish tacos is impressive with huge servings of fried catfish.cornbread is soft yet dense . Chicken on waffles with maple syrup..with waffles baked crispy at edges yet fluffy. will be back for sure!
Ordered the 3 musketeers.bringal/bitteegourd/long bean perfectly stirred fried.prawns in peppercorn was nice too but not for mapou toufu- over spicy for my bud. No fantastic to entice my sec trip bk
Vegetarian buffet worth of $24.8 for a gd spread of delectable vegetarian dishes . Well balanced spread of healthy cooked meal instead of lotsa of starchy flour dishes .will definitely bk for more !!
Avocado wif melaka was nice but exorbitant at $7!! Dessicate coconut with vanilla ice cream on soft spongy waffles wasn't  my ideal crispy waffles .overall mediocre .. Wil try chock next rnd
Oysters definitely succulent !Side dishes nothing to rave abt.Salmon tartare too salty.diver scallop too bland.lobster roll cld make do wif.Mud crab thinly shredded for any fulfillment.bk for main.
Truffle infused cream salmon and mushrm linguine is yummylicious ! The big one is too highly priced for the normal ingredients.

Price is so economical.tried laksa/ nasi lemak / green curry / chicken rice /mango wif sticky rice ..all cleared my taste bud except for siew mai- skin wrappin and mock Meat wasn't too ideal .bk again
Sashimi chewy to almst real! Smoked duck & rms mus try ! Fried Shitake rms with cheese is heaven ! buckwheat noodle was chewy wif gd soup base.claypot mix veg/sesame icecream/seaweed rice is common.

venue.name: 藤素食 Teng Bespoke Vegetarian Dining

tip.text: King of sea wif crispy miso infused salmon n miserable prawns for the hefty price tag.duck leg Confit crispy on outside. .gd. .cm bk for view only

tip.text: Fish and chipskinda bland .mushrm pizza was k.vegetarian baked rice was cheesy nice .seafood aglio well olived.breading pudding k.molten chocolate  too sweet but  acceptably well with vanilla icecream
Crayfish mussel pasta is perfect! Chicken fajitas is toasted to crisp ! Honey peach soda was mediocre
Cedar salmon pasta great chunk of salmon ..adored the jack Daniel salmon wif jack Daniel glaze - fantastically chargrilled ! Will be back for more mains !
Burger for the vegan souls ! Wholemeal burger wif succulent mock meat n zesty pineapple for satay and mushrm burger was nice 2 .broccoli was 2 raw 4 our taste bud. Fries is nvr enuff 4 us.

seafood aglio was perfectly olive.battered fish n chip was crusted n delectable crispy. Funghi pizza lotsa mushrm thinly Crusted pizza veg pasta was nice.all except nachos with uneven spread of cheese
Few pcs of Unagi wif curry ..pork burger was nice ..redbean matcha was acceptably sweet.

tip.text: Lava cake with deep oozing  of rich chocolate and ice cream .definitely back for.more !!seafood aglio olio was well oiled with olive and milky mango latte was worth ordering with mango cubes within !!
Red velvet waffles with dark chocolate within the waffles . On top laid the sour cream and vanilla icecream that blends well with the moist waffles.toffee latte wasn't  fantastic as raved
Well known  is the red velvet waffles filled with chocolate filling within . Cream cheese was laid on top and goes well with the moist waffles. Nice blend . Toffee latte wasn't fantastic as raved.
Classic fish and chips with homemade beer batter . Fish is tender juicy and flaky .definitely back again !

venue.name: Fatboy's The Burger Bar @ Holland Village

tip.text: Smoked salmon along side hashbrwn egg Salad. .normal brunch but gd. . Almond latte is rich with almond taste ..highly recommended !
Lavender latte mild with no tinge of slight lavender .raved pancake was normal and pricey at $12 .salmon sandwich with few miserable pieces of salmon. Overall price slightly steep . Will go if nearby
Fragrant pandan ice cream on crispy and fluffy waffles is just the right combination with line of gula melaka to perfect it .
2 poached eggs seated well with  slices of salmon pieces on brioche bread . A hot chocolate to complement a gd brunch
the salmon was fresh and flaky,seasoned with Miso & crispy/ smokey Salmon skin.comes with sweet & refreshing Apple and Fennel  along wif fruit puree at the side. worth the $22 price tag.
Buckwheat soba in this set with teppanyaki salmon , shimsahmo salmon salad .sallop rice worth only 33.80 was worth ordering !! Can try soba water upon entering ..it complimentary with order .
this rest served gd western fare . Had ordered cheese mozarella nachos, the fish in lemon butter fish, honey mustard chicken and beef fondue were all highly favored!Definitely bk!

formattedAddress: #01-03, The Cannery, Clarke Quay (3D River Valley Rd)

tip.text: Tucked in quiet lane of yio chu Kang. Local fare over here but steeply priced . Fried crab seafood was fragantly stirred , fried bringals was not deeply fried to certain crispness . Horfun mediocre.
Matcha with scones.. iced caramel latte Is just the right degree of sweetness
Service needs improvement .their grilled options r delectable!Grilled prawn n fish fillet n mixed meat combo fantastic ! Cosy plx for Lebanese meal !baklawah dessert r explosive.not enough with 4pcs

Scallop is succulent.salmon/seabass/redsnapper was cooked in different methods that I left nothing on the plate! dessert chocolately is thumbs up. Soft n coarse ingredients jus melt perfectly in mouth
Gd chilax against waterfront ..truffle fries is nice with beer .
Yam ring with generous fillings ..sambal fish too spicy ..cereal prawns is gd. .fried roll prawns with mango is mediocre but can try once ...sea cucumber texture tasted so real !!!

venue.name: Classic Lao Di Fang Vegetarian Restaurant

tip.text: Salmon pieces r miserably small ... not really fulfilling ..some animated collectibles on display ..for a small get together plx
Self service is fine 4 me here but the cod fish with chip was tasteless with soggy broiled chips I supposed .. gota dip wif lotsa sauce 2 flavor it .. won't b back unless happen 2 pass by

venue.name: Smiths Authentic British Fish And Chips

tip.text: Try the walnut maple n not rum n rasin. ..found it 2 strong & bitter 4 me.interior was cosy for laid back wif diff lights decor
Thin crust pizza ..crispy ...tortilla wif layer of icing ontop was different indeed ! Ocean platter was small a portion for 4 pax ...sambal fish was nice ..banana crumple n brownie thumbs up !

Food is below mediocre .baked brown rice still edible .noodle texture is dry with hint of gravy of olive oil will be better . pizza is really not worth mentioning with miserable serving of ingredients
Seafood buffet .. egg yolk crab and raw oysters r always my fav ! Not forgetting Alaska crab !! Wil be back again
Grilled mackerel is Damm tasty . Food is delectable with economical price tag.

formattedAddress: #B1-50 Liang Court Shopping Centre (177 River Valley Road)

tip.text: Fried rat mee is nice and cordycep soup is nourishing .. only setback is the limited 6options daily in their menu .. if around that area ...then only will I think about heading back to the small cafe
Coffee latte and banoffee cake nothing to scream abt.  Small quaint heartland cafe ...but service was warm welcomin. .. curry egg mayo was nice In a big croissant ..might not head back again
Jap foodie was never labeled as unaffordable over here as all so economically priced !!!:-)luv the unagi teapot rice ..the fried prawn pancake roast belly pork n caramel desert not to miss !

venue.name: Sun With Moon Japanese Dining & Café

tip.text: Aglio olio nothing to rave about .. blandless ..but mushroom pizza was delectable with gd servin of rooms and cheesy n perfectly baked to crisp .. Wil go bk for chilax session !
Damn breathtaking... tranquil way of relaxing by the sea ..out ...exclusivity of only 50units ! Recommended !!
Dun opt for the curry prawns too chewy !Satay/mutton/curry mushroom Is delectable .stir mixed veggie is raw 4!Curry fish head dosent has the authentic taste.tahu goreng is like food court standard

Service was slow but food was reasonably priced and mediocre . Ordered the sambal fish and tofu claypot.  was nice ...fish and chip was a bit disappointing as tasted more like potato croquet than fish
Liked their green curry / mushrm burger  and Mexican tortillas. Overall acceptable but abit overpriced given such location
Mushroom has always been my favorite ..so is the pizza over here ! Potato potage is not so nice with fries lay beneath topped off with cheese...banana ice cream was kinda of mediocre ...

Tucked In a small corner of jln besar,  herbal chicken soup was damm thumb up ...not so much into battered mushrm. ..roast duck seemed like real stuff with the roasted skin alike !!claypot veggie nice
Bbq salmon n scallops r succulent !!wil definitely head 4 again !!
Sambal sotong / toufu / straw rice / fungus with mushroom and ginkgo. ... food are good but waiting time a bit slow.
